  "prompt": "How I will get work visa for usa?",
  "response": "To obtain a work visa for the USA, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Job Offer\n- Secure a job offer from a US employer willing to sponsor your work visa\n\n2. Visa Types\nCommon work visas include:\n- H-1B (Specialty occupation workers)\n- L-1 (Intracompany transferees)\n- O-1 (Individuals with extraordinary ability)\n- E-3 (Australian professionals)\n\n3. Employer Sponsorship\n- Employer must file a petition with USCIS (Form I-129)\n- Obtain Labor Condition Application (LCA) from Department of Labor\n\n4. Required Documents\n- Valid passport\n- Job offer letter\n- Approved USCIS petition\n- Educational qualifications\n- Professional experience certificates\n- Proof of specialized skills\n\n5. Visa Application Process\n- Complete DS-160 online application\n- Pay visa application fees\n- Schedule and attend visa interview at US Embassy/Consulate\n- Provide biometric information\n\n6. Additional Requirements\n- Meet specific visa category qualifications\n- Demonstrate intent to return to home country\n- Pass background and health checks\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Consult immigration lawyer\n- Check specific visa requirements\n- Prepare comprehensive documentation",
